{{Infobox person | name = Andra Gavrilović | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Андра Гавриловић | birth_date = {{Birth date|1864|07|11}} | birth_place = [[Svilajnac]], [[Principality of Serbia]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1929|02|24|1864|07|11}} | death_place = [[Belgrade]], [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]] | nationality = Serbian, Yugoslavian | other_names = | occupation = historian, historian of literature, writer and diplomat | known_for = }}
'''Andra Gavrilović''' ({{lang-sr|Андра Гавриловић}}; [[Svilajnac]], [[Principality of Serbia]] 11 July 1864 — [[Belgrade]], [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]] 24 February 1929) was Serbian historian, historian of literature, writer and diplomat.
He also specialized in works of [[Dositej Obradović]].<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AQpPAAAAYAAJ&q=andra+gavrilovic+istoricar&dq=andra+gavrilovic+istoricar&hl=sr&sa=X&ei=TUWZUKSnBKGV0QXdwYHgDw&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAA | title=Izraz | year=1989 | issue=7-8 | publisher=Hrvatska naklada | page=27|quote= Andra Gavrilović, jedan od vrednih radnika na proučavanju istorije srpske književnosti, zaslužan za bliže poznavanje Dositeja i njegovog doba, uzeo je u odbranu Dositeja}}</ref>
Gavrilović disagreed with opinion of [[Jovan Tomić]] that figure of [[Djemo the Mountaineer]] was based on Jegen Osman Pasha. In his polemic work 'Who wasn't Djemo the Mountaineer, correction of someone's literary-historical mistake' ({{lang-sr|Ко није био Ђемо Брђанин, исправка туђе литерарно-историске грешке}}).<ref name="Letopis">{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=42dFAAAAYAAJ&q=%D0%93%D0%B0%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%9B+%D0%82%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%BE+%D0%B1%D1%80%D1%92%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%BD&dq=%D0%93%D0%B0%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%9B+%D0%82%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%BE+%D0%B1%D1%80%D1%92%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%BD&source=bl&ots=AizGSF5ddj&sig=peIxjYQdlNq_GNKBreMPvoTUb6M&hl=en&sa=X&ei=XatuUPq_BMvKswac64DwCQ&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAQ | title=Letopis Matice srpske | journal=Letopis Matice srpske | year=1902 | volume=211 | issue=16}}</ref> he emphasized that Djemo was in fact [[Albanian nobility|Albanian nobleman]] Gjin Muzaki because he assumed that [[Serbian epic poetry]] about struggle between [[Prince Marko|Marko Kraljević]] and Djemo the Mountaneer was based on real struggles between Prince Marko and [[Muzaka family]] from [[Albania (toponym)|Albania]].<ref>{{cite book | title=Karadžić |url= https://books.google.com/books?ei=qTKZUJ7EMs7RsgbTv4G4BA&hl=sr&id=ZrLYAAAAMAAJ&dq=%D1%92%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%BE+%D0%B1%D1%80%D1%92%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%BD+%D1%92%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%BE&q=%D0%93%D0%B0%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%9B#search_anchor | publisher=Štamparija Mate Jovanovnića | year=1900 | location=Belgrade | page=26}}</ref>
According to Andra Gavrilović the figure of [[Vuča General]] is based on Tanush Dukagjin, a member of [[Dukagjini family|Dukagjini noble family]] from Albania.<ref>{{cite journal | title=Sitni prilozi | author=Stanoje Stanojević, Dušan J. Popović | journal=Glasnik | year=1937 | volume=10 | page=213 | quote=Спомињемо, по дужности, раније још нагађање А. Гавриловића у чланку Историјска се- ћања у неким нар. песмама о Краље- вићу Марку (Глас СКАк. 1*\Ш1), по коме је: „Вуча џенерал Танусије (Та- нуш), родоначелник Дукађина, којисе зове још и Вуно и Вуко...}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=none| author=Srpska akademija nauka i umetnosti | journal=Glas | year=1900 | volume=58-60 | page=134 | quote=Идући у мислима тим правцем, сусрећемо се с родоначелником Дукађина, познатим нам већ Тану- сијем, који се зове још и Вуно или Вуко1 и који је у Задрим.ьу био западни сусед Вукашннова Призрена. Овај Латинин Вуко}}</ref>
