'''Te Iki-o-te-rangi Pouwhare''' (1880&ndash;1963) was a New Zealand tribal leader, historian and genealogist. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Tuhoe]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Te Houhi]], [[Wanganui]], [[New Zealand]] in about 1880.<ref name="DNZB Pouwhare">{{DNZB|title=Te Iki-o-te-rangi Pouwhare|first= Robert Marunui Iki|last= Pouwhare|id=4p20|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

