[[File:Roman Empire - Africa Proconsularis (125 AD).svg|thumb|right|Africa Proconsularis (125 AD)]]
'''Tigimma''' was during the [[Roman Empire]] a [[civitas]] of [[Africa Proconsularis]]. The town has been tentatively identified with ruins near [[Djemaa Saharidj|Djemâa]].

The town was also the [[cathedra|seat]] of an ancient Christian [[bishopric]]<ref>[http://www.apostolische-nachfolge.de/titulare_t.htm Apostolische Nachfolge – Tigimma].</ref>
Which survives today as a [[titular see]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t1788.htm  Tigimma] at gcatholic.org.</ref> and the current [[bishop]] is [[Stanislaw Dowlaszewicz]], who replaced [[Luciano Storero]] in 2000.<ref>''Le Petit Episcopologe'', Issue 162, Number 13,930.</ref>

